      • getExecutionTargetTimeStamp

        public TimeStamp getExecutionTargetTimeStamp()
        Specifies when an order must be executed. This could be relevant when using the paper broker implementation. It also reflects a "good starting at".

        An executionPoint of null expresses that the order is executed as soon as possible (does not collide with Time In Force, as TIF is used at the broker's/exchange's end).

        Specified by:
        getExecutionTargetTimeStamp in interface IOrder
